[I've been trying to think about possible epidemiologic links where this virus may have originated, waiting for laboratory genetic studies and can't help but wonder if perhaps Ukraine might be involved. The 1 Acute Flaccid Paralysis (AFP) case and geographic location of positive environmental samples suggest the ultra-orthodox Jewish community is involved (Rockland County, parts of NYC although the exact location(s?) within NYC have not been announced. In 2021, Ukraine identified 2 AFP cases associated with cVDPV2. There are pilgrimage sites that ultra-orthodox communities around the world visit in Uman Ukraine, the former home of a revered Rabbi known for rejuvenating the ultra-orthodox movement in the late 18th and early 19th centuries. (see https://sacredsites.com/europe/ukraine/sacred_sites_of_ukraine.html for a discussion and map of holy sites in Ukraine).

That being said, it appears as though the UK had circulation of the virus since February 2022, predating the USA by 2-3 months (1st circulation noted in May 2022), so travel between the UK and many countries in Africa or outside of Africa (including Pakistan and Afghanistan) where cVDPV2 outbreaks have been identified in 2021 and 2022 (see "see also" below) is a possibility. Hopefully, genetic testing will clarify the journey of the involved virus, but the major point here is that importations have occurred into countries with pockets of unvaccinated individuals and the virus(es) are being easily transmitted in these pockets.

Note, that while the case in Israel occurred in March 2022, the virus involved was officially reported as a cVDPV3 (see Poliomyelitis update (11): global cVDPV2, cVDPV3, RFI 20220311.8701925). I am now wondering if this is a 2nd event, or a further clarification of the earlier event and the virus identified.

My semantic question is with the continued identification of positive environmental samples for VDPV2 in the USA (New York state now including NYC) and other parts of London, at what point can we refer to this virus as a cVDPV2? (https://bit.ly/3dtd807 and https://www.who.int/news-room/questions-and-answers/item/poliomyelitis-vaccine-derived-polio) - Mod.MPP]

