Poliovirus Weekly Update as of 10 Aug 2022, World Health Organization
---------------------------------------------------------------------
New wild poliovirus isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 0
Environment: 8
Others: 0

New cVDPV isolates reported this week:
AFP cases: 36
Environment: 11
Others: 7

Summary of new polioviruses this week:
- Afghanistan: 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample
- Pakistan: 7 WPV1 positive environmental samples
- Algeria: 3 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples
- DR Congo: 9 cVDPV2 cases
- Ghana: 1 cVDPV2 positive environmental sample
-Madagascar: 7 cVDPV1 positive environmental samples
- Mozambique: 1 cVDPV1 case
- Yemen: 26 cVDPV2 cases

Afghanistan
• No new wild poliovirus type 1 (WPV1) or circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) cases were reported this week. There is 1 WPV1 case reported in 2022 and 4 in 2021. The total number of cVDPV2 cases remains 43.
• 1 WPV1 positive environmental sample was reported in Kunar.

Pakistan
• No new wild poliovirus type 1 case was reported this week. The number of 2022 cases remains 14. In 2021, the number of WVP1 cases was 1 and the number of cVDPV2 cases was 8.
• 7 WPV1 positive environmental samples were reported; 4 in Khyber Pakhtunkhwa, 2 in Punjab and 1 in Islamabad.

Algeria
• No case of circulating vaccine-derived poliovirus type 2 (cVDPV2) was reported this week. There is 1 case in 2022 that is linked to the Zamfara emergence from Nigeria.
• 3 cVDPV2 positive environmental samples were reported in Tamanghasset.

