ProMED

[Similar to the week before, this past week has been an active week for poliovirus identification. There are multiple positive WPV1 isolates from ESs in Pakistan and 1 in Afghanistan, cVDPV1 AFP case in Mozambique and positive ES in Madagascar, and cVDPV2 AFP casaes in the DR Congo and Yemen and positive ES samples in Algeria and Ghana.

This is a reminder that the presence of cVDPVs occurs when there are lower than protective vaccine coverages and a sign that if a poliovirus (be it a WPV or a VDPV) is introduced, it can easily be transmitted in the communities.

A map showing the locations of each confirmed case of polio worldwide in the past 12 months can be found at https://polioeradication.org/polio-today/polio-now/. One can see cases of cVDPV in a band across Africa and in Israel, Ukraine, Tajikistan, Afghanistan, and Pakistan; cVDPV1 in Madagascar and Yemen, and WPV1 in Afghanistan, Pakistan, Malawi and Mozambique. - Mod.MPP

ProMED map:
Worldwide: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=8705016,8854]
